Lazy Lamu chiefs will soon be fired if they do not change, the Lamu county commissioner has warned.The chiefs have been warned told to contain and establish the cause of increasing crimes in their locations. Joseph Kanyiri on Sunday said chiefs must take their jobs seriously and reduce or completely eradicate crime.He said his office will not hesitate to fire lazy chiefs who have become more of an expense than a help to the security of the county.Kanyiri urged the chiefs to deal with illicit brew, narcotic drug use, child labour, conflict and children dropping out of school. He said they will evaluate their performance and decide whether the chiefs will retain their positions.